headline: Taiwan Must Help US to Make Half Its Chips, Commerce Chief Says
summary: The US has held discussions about that with Taipei to reduce the risks of over-reliance, Commerce Secretary Howard Lutnick said in an interview with NewsNation.  “That’s been the conversation we had with Taiwan, that you have to understand it’s vital for you to have us produce 50%,” he said.  US officials have for years warned about an over-dependence on Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. and its giant ecosystem of suppliers, which together make and supply the vast majority of the world’s most advanced chips.
